# Contributing to VP Cloud SDK

Thank you for your interest in the VP Cloud SDK! This document provides important information about how the SDK is structured and how to report issues.

## Important: All Code is Autogenerated

**This SDK is entirely autogenerated from the OpenAPI specification.** All source files in this SDK are code-generated and will be overwritten during the next regeneration. As such, **we do not accept pull requests (PRs) for any changes to the SDK codebase.**

## Reporting Issues

If you encounter any issues with the SDK, including:
- Bugs or errors in generated code
- Missing or incorrect API models
- Documentation issues
- Feature requests

**Please create a GitHub issue** with:
- A clear description of the problem
- Steps to reproduce (if applicable)
- Expected vs. actual behavior
- SDK version and Python version
- Any relevant error messages or logs

For urgent issues or questions, you can also contact Voltage Park support directly at support@voltagepark.com.

## Support

For API support, questions, or urgent issues, please contact:
- **Email**: support@voltagepark.com

Thank you for helping improve the VP Cloud SDK!
